issue.body:
When trying to login after you logout there's a leftover `Authorization` in the ApiService header which will make ` path('auth-token', obtain_auth_token),` from the backend to return `Forbidden` . The workaround is to change the `postCredential` method from `auth.service.js` from

  postCredential(data) {
    return this.request.post('/auth-token', data)
  }
}

to 

  postCredential(data) {
    this.request.removeHeader() // clear the header before posting.
    return this.request.post('/auth-token', data)
  }
}

or even better just clear that particular header before posting the login credentials.

 removeAuth() {
    delete this.instance.defaults.headers.common["Authorization"]
  }
